main event: A bright ball of orange light was observed during the ascent of a rocket booster launched from Cape Canaveral.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 20 minutes,The object was noted to be red, white, and blue with red leading during its ascent,The event was visually confirmed by multiple observations around the same date,Similar bright lights were reported in different instances east of Cape Canaveral,The sighting was formally recorded in a Project Blue Book document that includes marine data from the U.S. Navy.
location: Atlantic, E of Cape Canaveral, USA
witness description: Observation documented in a Project Blue Book record card.
